WEBVTT

00:08.467 --> 00:11.262
- THIS IS WHAT YOU MISSED
LAST WEEK ON SHAMELESS.

00:11.262 --> 00:12.972
IT WAS A GREAT EPISODE.

00:12.972 --> 00:14.849
- OH, DEBBIE.
DEBBIE, STOP.

00:14.849 --> 00:16.350
- DON'T YOU WANT TO?
- SOMEDAY.

00:16.350 --> 00:18.686
- WELL, WHY NOT NOW?
- 'CAUSE YOU'RE 13.

00:18.686 --> 00:21.981
- IT TURNS OUT I'M 1/32
MENOMINEE INDIAN.

00:21.981 --> 00:23.482
- YOU'RE EVEN FOXIER IN PERSON.

00:23.482 --> 00:25.276
- YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
THAT YOU HAD KIDS.

00:25.276 --> 00:28.028
- THIS IS DALE, BEN, SARAH,
DENISE, AND GARY.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.864
- I STUDIED MY ASS OFF
FOR THIS TEST.

00:29.864 --> 00:31.866
- I'M SORRY.

00:34.034 --> 00:35.619
- I HAVE THIS LIVER CONDITION.

00:35.619 --> 00:37.621
PRETTY MUCH KICKED.
THEY SAY I NEED A NEW ONE.

00:37.621 --> 00:40.124
I NEVER HEAR OF AN INDIAN
GETTING A LIVER TRANSPLANT.

00:40.124 --> 00:42.127
- WE USE A SWEAT LODGE.

00:42.127 --> 00:44.545
CLEANS YOUR LIVER, YOUR SPLEEN,
AND IT'S A REAL HIGH.

00:44.545 --> 00:46.297
- FRANK?
[siren wails]

00:46.297 --> 00:48.133
- HOW'D YOU GUYS START
GETTING IT ON?

00:48.133 --> 00:49.550
- I GOT HIM DRUNK AND ALMOST
FUCKED HIM IN A TENT.

00:49.550 --> 00:53.053
I CAN GET A LITTLE WILD.

00:53.053 --> 00:54.722
I'M NOT TELLING HIM.
THIS DID NOT HAPPEN.

00:54.722 --> 00:57.516
- YOU GOT OFF ON IT
AS MUCH AS I DID.

00:57.516 --> 00:59.102
[both gasp]
- GOD DAMN IT!

00:59.102 --> 01:00.144
- WHAT?
- MIKE, I DON'T KNOW WHAT HE--

01:00.144 --> 01:01.395
- PLEASE, JUST GO.

01:01.395 --> 01:03.189
- WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:03.189 --> 01:05.774
- MY WAY OF APOLOGIZING.
NOW IT'S A PARTY.

01:09.237 --> 01:10.237
- OH!
[laughs]

01:10.237 --> 01:11.530
- FIONA!

01:11.530 --> 01:12.656
HE'S NOT BREATHING!

01:12.656 --> 01:14.159
both:
OH, MY GOD!

01:14.159 --> 01:15.409
- WHAT'S ON HIS FACE?
- OH, MY GOD.

01:15.409 --> 01:17.203
HE GOT INTO MY COKE.
- WHO'S FIONA?

01:17.203 --> 01:19.079
- THAT'S ME.
- FIONA GALLAGHER...

01:19.079 --> 01:20.122
YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO REMAIN SILENT.

01:20.122 --> 01:21.832
ANYTHING YOU SAY CAN

01:21.832 --> 01:23.209
AND WILL BE USED AGAINST YOU
IN A COURT OF LAW.

01:23.209 --> 01:25.211
[indistinct radio chatter,
siren wails]

01:31.134 --> 01:34.137
[High Strung's
The Luck You Got]

01:34.137 --> 01:38.098
♪ ♪

01:38.098 --> 01:41.310
- ♪ THINK OF ALL THE LUCK
YOU GOT ♪

01:41.310 --> 01:44.480
♪ KNOW THAT
IT'S NOT FOR NAUGHT ♪

01:44.480 --> 01:47.525
♪ YOU WERE BEAMING
ONCE BEFORE ♪

01:47.525 --> 01:51.820
♪ BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
ANYMORE ♪

01:51.820 --> 01:55.366
♪ WHAT IS THIS DOWNSIDE ♪

01:55.366 --> 01:58.619
♪ THAT YOU SPEAK OF? ♪

01:58.619 --> 02:00.955
♪ WHAT IS THIS FEELING ♪

02:00.955 --> 02:05.334
♪ YOU'RE SO SURE OF? ♪

02:05.334 --> 02:12.258
♪ ♪

02:12.258 --> 02:15.553
♪ ROUND UP THE FRIENDS
YOU GOT ♪

02:15.553 --> 02:18.806
♪ KNOW THAT
THEY'RE NOT FOR NAUGHT ♪

02:18.806 --> 02:22.268
♪ YOU WERE WILLING
ONCE BEFORE ♪

02:22.268 --> 02:26.188
♪ BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT
ANYMORE ♪

02:26.188 --> 02:29.608
♪ WHAT IS THIS DOWNSIDE ♪

02:29.608 --> 02:33.320
♪ THAT YOU SPEAK OF? ♪

02:33.320 --> 02:35.281
♪ WHAT IS THIS FEELING ♪

02:35.281 --> 02:39.034
♪ YOU'RE SO SURE OF? ♪

02:41.495 --> 02:45.708
[woman speaking indistinctly
over PA]

02:48.836 --> 02:50.754
[beeping, keys clacking]

02:50.754 --> 02:53.007
- LOOK AT THE CAMERA.

03:26.373 --> 03:29.043
- [sighs]

03:29.043 --> 03:31.587
THEY PROBABLY TOOK HER
TO DISTRICT 6 FOR BOOKING.

03:31.587 --> 03:33.381
THAT'S WHERE
THEY USUALLY TAKE YOU

03:33.381 --> 03:35.841
BEFORE THEY TRANSFER YOU
TO COUNTY.

03:35.841 --> 03:37.384
SHE'S GONNA NEED A LAWYER.

03:37.384 --> 03:40.638
YOU GOT ANYBODY
YOU WANT US TO CALL?

03:40.638 --> 03:42.640
LIP?
- YEAH?

03:45.310 --> 03:48.395
- IS THERE A LAWYER
YOU WANT US TO USE?

03:48.395 --> 03:51.565
I USED A GUY ON CALUMET
A COUPLE YEARS AGO

03:51.565 --> 03:54.276
FOR THAT D.U.I. THING I HAD,
YOU KNOW?

03:54.276 --> 03:57.322
[sighs] HE SMELLS
LIKE DIRTY DISH TOWELS,

03:57.322 --> 03:58.697
BUT IF YOU BREATHE THROUGH
YOUR MOUTH, IT'S BEARABLE.

03:58.697 --> 04:00.908
- FIONA GALLAGHER?
- PHILIP GALLAGHER.

04:00.908 --> 04:02.618
- IS FIONA HERE?
- NO.

04:02.618 --> 04:04.078
- WILL SHE BE BACK?
- NO, NOT SOON.

04:04.078 --> 04:05.746
I'M--I'M LIAM'S BROTHER.

04:05.746 --> 04:06.997
- IS THERE ANOTHER PARENT
OR LEGAL GUARDIAN AVAILABLE?

04:06.997 --> 04:08.791
- NO.
IS LIAM GONNA BE OKAY?

04:08.791 --> 04:10.584
- I'M SORRY. I REALLY NEED
A RESPONSIBLE ADULT PRESENT--

04:10.584 --> 04:13.170
- LOOK, MY MOM'S A BIPOLAR DRUG
ADDICT WHO SPLIT YEARS AGO,

04:13.170 --> 04:15.465
AND MY DAD'S A DRUNK, AND
THE COPS JUST HAULED FIONA OFF

04:15.465 --> 04:17.257
TO JAIL, OKAY?
- [sighs]

04:17.257 --> 04:19.468
- LOOK, I'M THE ONLY THING THAT
PASSES FOR A RESPONSIBLE ADULT

04:19.468 --> 04:23.764
THAT YOU'RE GONNA FIND.
NOW, HOW IS LIAM?

04:23.764 --> 04:26.434
- YOUR BROTHER CAME IN
WITH ACUTE COCAINE TOXICITY--

04:26.434 --> 04:28.686
DISORIENTED, HALLUCINATING,
AND WITH A DANGEROUSLY

04:28.686 --> 04:30.270
ELEVATED HEART RATE.

04:30.270 --> 04:32.481
HE'S ON NALOXONE
FOR HIS ALTERED MENTAL STATUS

04:32.481 --> 04:34.692
AND BENZODIAZEPINE
TO CONTROL HIS SEIZURES.

04:34.692 --> 04:35.943
- SEIZURES?
- [sighs]

04:35.943 --> 04:37.487
WE'RE MONITORING
HIS TEMPERATURE,

04:37.487 --> 04:38.821
HIS HEART RATE,
AND HIS GLUCOSE LEVELS,

04:38.821 --> 04:40.864
BUT HE HAS STARTED
TO SETTLE DOWN.

04:40.864 --> 04:42.491
- CAN WE SEE HIM?

04:42.491 --> 04:44.327
- I'M SORRY. ONLY IMMEDIATE
FAMILY MEMBERS OVER 18

04:44.327 --> 04:45.744
ARE ALLOWED IN THE PICU.

04:45.744 --> 04:49.332
- GO. WE'LL STAY HERE
WITH CARL AND DEBS.

04:52.751 --> 04:56.171
[indistinct chatter]

05:28.495 --> 05:32.458
[woman coughing]

05:38.964 --> 05:42.718
[monitor beeping]

05:48.891 --> 05:51.518
- YOU CAN TOUCH HIM.

05:51.518 --> 05:54.146
- WHY IS HE, UH, TIED DOWN?

05:54.146 --> 05:56.565
- HE WAS AGITATED
AND HURTING HIMSELF.

05:56.565 --> 05:59.777
IT'S NOT UNUSUAL
IN COCAINE OVERDOSES.

05:59.777 --> 06:02.112
- IS HE GONNA BE OKAY?

06:02.112 --> 06:03.614
- WELL, IT'S EARLY YET,

06:03.614 --> 06:06.283
BUT COCAINE OVERDOSES
AREN'T USUALLY FATAL.

06:06.283 --> 06:07.868
HE DID HAVE SEVERAL SEIZURES,

06:07.868 --> 06:11.789
AND THAT CAN LEAD
TO INTELLECTUAL DECLINE.

06:11.789 --> 06:13.207
- BRAIN DAMAGE?

06:13.207 --> 06:14.875
- LEARNING
AND LANGUAGE PROBLEMS,

06:14.875 --> 06:17.711
EMOTIONAL
AND BEHAVIORAL DISORDERS.

06:17.711 --> 06:20.506
THE DEVELOPING BRAIN
IS DELICATE.

06:20.506 --> 06:23.426
YOU'RE GONNA NEED TO CONSULT
WITH A PEDIATRIC NEUROLOGIST

06:23.426 --> 06:26.512
TO MONITOR ANY POSSIBLE
LONG-TERM DEFICITS.

06:30.516 --> 06:33.393
LOOK, YOUR LITTLE BROTHER IS A--
HE'S A TOUGH GUY.

06:33.393 --> 06:35.229
HE'S STRONG.

06:35.229 --> 06:36.480
IF I WAS A BETTING WOMAN,

06:36.480 --> 06:39.233
MY MONEY WOULD BE
ON A FULL RECOVERY.

06:49.494 --> 06:52.454
- [softly] IT'S OKAY.
HERE WE GO. SHH.

07:04.758 --> 07:07.386
[door opens]

07:07.386 --> 07:08.804
- TRANSPORT VAN IS HERE.

07:08.804 --> 07:10.889
LADIES.

07:12.432 --> 07:13.433
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?

07:13.433 --> 07:15.853
- DIVISION 4 FOR PROCESSING.

07:15.853 --> 07:18.063
PUT YOUR HANDS UP.
- MY BROTHER'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

07:18.063 --> 07:20.732
I-I NEED TO MAKE A CALL
AND FIND OUT HOW HE'S DOING.

07:20.732 --> 07:23.527
- YOU'LL HAVE ACCESS TO A PHONE
AFTER INTAKE AT DIVISION 4.

07:23.527 --> 07:25.529
SET?
LET'S GO. COME ON.

07:25.529 --> 07:28.532
[rock music]

07:28.532 --> 07:36.582
♪ ♪

08:02.274 --> 08:05.695
[elevator bell dings]

08:11.867 --> 08:14.745
- ANYTHING NEW?
[sighs]

08:14.745 --> 08:17.456
WE GOT DEB AND CARL INTO BED.
V IS GONNA STAY WITH THEM.

08:17.456 --> 08:18.999
AND I GOT A HOLD OF THE COPS.

08:18.999 --> 08:21.084
THEY'RE MOVING FIONA
TO WOMEN'S COUNTY.

08:21.084 --> 08:24.087
WE CAN CATCH UP TO HER OVER
THERE FOR HER ARRAIGNMENT.

08:24.087 --> 08:26.089
WHAT'S THAT?

08:26.089 --> 08:28.800
- IT'S ADMISSIONS PAPERWORK.

08:28.800 --> 08:31.094
"INSURANCE"?
NONE.

08:31.094 --> 08:33.347
"EMPLOYER"?
NONE.

08:33.347 --> 08:37.476
"CREDIT CARD NUMBER"?
NONE.

08:37.476 --> 08:39.519
JESUS.

08:39.519 --> 08:42.230
MAYBE THEY'LL LET US WASH DISHES
IN THE CAFETERIA.

08:42.230 --> 08:43.857
- NO, FUCK THAT.
THEY GOT TO TREAT HIM.

08:43.857 --> 08:45.651
THEY'RE NOT GONNA KICK
A SICK TODDLER TO THE CURB

08:45.651 --> 08:47.235
'CAUSE HE DOESN'T HAVE
A GOLD CARD.

08:47.235 --> 08:48.904
- THAT DOESN'T MEAN

08:48.904 --> 08:50.656
THEY'RE NOT GONNA SEND
A COLLECTION AGENCY OUR WAY.

08:50.656 --> 08:52.074
- WHAT, YOU'RE WORRIED

08:52.074 --> 08:53.909
THEY'RE GONNA FUCK UP
YOUR CREDIT RATING?

08:53.909 --> 08:56.578
FIONA'S BAIL HEARING
IS AROUND NOON SOMETIME.

08:56.578 --> 08:57.996
I LEFT A MESSAGE
WITH THAT LAWYER.

08:57.996 --> 09:00.625
- NO.
- NO, WHAT?

09:00.625 --> 09:02.668
- UH, LAWYER WORK FOR FREE?

09:02.668 --> 09:04.419
- V AND I CAN FRONT YOU
SOME CASH.

09:04.419 --> 09:05.837
- WHAT, FRONT US SOME CASH?

09:05.837 --> 09:07.547
LIKE WE'RE EVER GONNA BE ABLE
TO PAY YOU BACK?

09:07.547 --> 09:09.466
- SHE NEEDS A LAWYER.
- AND SHE'LL GET ONE.

09:09.466 --> 09:10.884
THE P.D.'S OFFICE
WILL HANDLE IT.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.636
- ARE YOU FUCKING KIDDING ME?

09:12.636 --> 09:15.055
AN OVERWORKED PUBLIC DEFENDER
STRAIGHT OUT OF LAW SCHOOL

09:15.055 --> 09:16.766
WITH A COUPLE HUNDRED CASES?

09:16.766 --> 09:20.102
- WORKS FOR ME.

09:20.102 --> 09:22.562
- IT WAS AN ACCIDENT, LIP.

09:22.562 --> 09:25.482
- IF YOU SAY SO.

09:25.482 --> 09:28.694
- THIS IS
SOME HEAVY SHIT, KID.

09:28.694 --> 09:31.947
ILLEGAL DRUGS,
A THREE-YEAR-OLD?

09:31.947 --> 09:34.574
SHE MIGHT END UP DOING
SOME SERIOUS TIME.

09:36.660 --> 09:39.371
SHE'S FAMILY.

09:45.210 --> 09:48.338
- IT'S ALMOST 5:00.

09:48.338 --> 09:52.009
I'VE GOT A QUANTUM PHYSICS QUIZ
IN THREE HOURS.

09:52.009 --> 09:54.094
GUESS I'M GONNA MISS IT, HUH?

09:58.598 --> 10:02.644
[monitor beeping]

10:10.778 --> 10:13.363
- YOU LOOK LIKE YOUR MOTHER.

10:13.363 --> 10:14.573
- WHAT?

10:14.573 --> 10:16.033
- SHE WAS A REAL LOOKER.

10:16.033 --> 10:19.578
- OH, MY GOD.
WE ALMOST LOST YOU.

10:19.578 --> 10:21.455
- SHE STILL A KNOCKOUT?

10:21.455 --> 10:22.790
- MY MOM?

10:22.790 --> 10:26.626
[chuckles]
NOT SO MUCH.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.962
LIFE HASN'T BEEN KIND.

10:28.962 --> 10:31.256
DIABETES--LOST A FOOT.

10:31.256 --> 10:33.633
BREAST CANCER BEFORE THAT--
DOUBLE MASTECTOMY.

10:33.633 --> 10:35.594
- BOTH OF 'EM, HUH?

10:35.594 --> 10:37.846
- MM.
THEY REBUILT THEM.

10:37.846 --> 10:39.264
DID A GOOD JOB TOO.

10:39.264 --> 10:40.725
SHE WAS ALWAYS COMPLAINING

10:40.725 --> 10:42.852
ABOUT HOW SHE WAS
A LITTLE SMALL UP THERE,

10:42.852 --> 10:45.645
SO SHE HAD THE DOC
ADD A COUPLE BRA SIZES.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.856
- SMALL?
I DON'T REMEMBER THAT.

10:47.856 --> 10:49.483
- COULDN'T REBUILD
THE NIPPLES, THOUGH,

10:49.483 --> 10:51.443
SO SHE HAD THEM TATTOOED ON.

10:51.443 --> 10:53.945
[both laugh]

10:53.945 --> 10:55.697
DID A PRETTY GOOD JOB TOO--

10:55.697 --> 10:57.574
EVEN UP CLOSE.
- HEY!

10:57.574 --> 11:00.827
LOOK WHO'S CONSCIOUS.
- HE JUST WOKE UP.

11:00.827 --> 11:02.954
THIS IS DR. ZABEL.
HE SAVED YOUR LIFE.

11:02.954 --> 11:06.083
- WELL, TEMPORARILY AT BEST.
HOW YOU FEELING, FRANK?

11:06.083 --> 11:08.085
- SHITTY.
DO I KNOW YOU?

11:08.085 --> 11:10.128
- SURE.
WE'RE OLD FRIENDS.

11:10.128 --> 11:12.714
ACCORDING TO YOUR EXTENSIVE
MEDICAL HISTORY,

11:12.714 --> 11:16.051
THIS IS YOUR 56TH VISIT
TO OUR HALLOWED HALL OF HEALING.

11:16.051 --> 11:17.677
YOU'RE A LEGEND
AROUND HERE, FRANK.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.513
TWO MORE VISITS,
YOU'LL PASS STERNO STAN

11:19.513 --> 11:21.348
AS OUR MOST DECORATED
FREQUENT FLYER.

11:21.348 --> 11:22.767
- [laughs]

11:22.767 --> 11:24.309
I REMEMBER YOU.

11:24.309 --> 11:27.104
YOU FUCKED UP
MY BEST HIGH EVER.

11:27.104 --> 11:28.856
- [laughs]
SILLY ME.

11:28.856 --> 11:31.776
I SHOULD HAVE SKIPPED
THE NARCAN, LET YOU OD.

11:31.776 --> 11:33.026
I SUSPECT
OUR BILLING DEPARTMENT

11:33.026 --> 11:34.779
WOULD HAVE SENT ME
ON A CARNIVAL CRUISE

11:34.779 --> 11:36.571
IF I JUST LET YOU CHOKE TO DEATH
ON YOUR OWN VOMIT.

11:36.571 --> 11:38.156
- NO, I WAS FINE.

11:38.156 --> 11:40.826
I'VE DONE FIVE SPEEDBALLS
BEFORE, NO PROBLEM-O.

11:40.826 --> 11:43.703
- NOW, ACCORDING
TO YOUR DAUGHTER HERE,

11:43.703 --> 11:46.206
YOU PASSED OUT IN A SWEAT LODGE?
- [chuckles]

11:46.206 --> 11:48.751
- BEYOND THE OBVIOUS QUESTION
OF WHERE YOU FOUND A SWEAT LODGE

11:48.751 --> 11:50.877
IN THE CITY OF CHICAGO
IN THE MIDDLE OF WINTER,

11:50.877 --> 11:52.755
WHAT IN GOD'S NAME
WERE YOU THINKING?

11:52.755 --> 11:55.715
- LIVER'S GIVING OUT,
NO TIME TO GET A NEW ONE.

11:55.715 --> 11:58.426
INDIANS SWEAT THE ALCOHOL OUT
AND LIVE FOREVER.

11:58.426 --> 11:59.804
- [chuckles]

11:59.804 --> 12:01.346
I REALIZE WESTERN MEDICINE

12:01.346 --> 12:02.806
ISN'T OFFERING YOU
MANY ALTERNATIVES, FRANK,

12:02.806 --> 12:05.725
BUT ALL THAT HOLISTIC CRAP
WILL KILL YOU FASTER.

12:05.725 --> 12:06.852
HOW LONG YOU BEEN A DRINKER?

12:06.852 --> 12:09.062
- STARTED WHEN I WAS 12.

12:09.062 --> 12:11.439
NEVER BREATHED
A SOBER BREATH SINCE,

12:11.439 --> 12:13.525
TILL THIS DAMN LIVER
QUIT DOING ITS JOB.

12:13.525 --> 12:15.485
- WHAT JOB IS THAT?

12:15.485 --> 12:17.070
- PROCESSING
THE COPIOUS AMOUNTS OF ALCOHOL

12:17.070 --> 12:18.488
I SEND ITS WAY DAILY.

12:18.488 --> 12:21.116
IF THERE WERE AN ANTI-A.A.,

12:21.116 --> 12:24.744
I'D HAVE A 40-YEAR DRUNK CHIP
RATTLING AROUND IN MY POCKET.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.204
[both chuckle]

12:26.204 --> 12:28.206
- GIVEN YOUR FOUR DECADES
OF STUMBLE-DOWN,

12:28.206 --> 12:29.541
HAMMERED-IN-THE-GUTTER
COMMITMENT

12:29.541 --> 12:30.793
TO PRO-LEVEL ALCOHOLISM...

12:30.793 --> 12:32.294
- THANK YOU.

12:32.294 --> 12:34.504
- I THINK YOU OWE YOUR LIVER
A CONDO IN BOCA

12:34.504 --> 12:36.006
AND SOME SHUFFLEBOARD.

12:36.006 --> 12:38.968
- [chuckles]

12:42.345 --> 12:46.099
- YOU KNOW
YOU'RE DYING, RIGHT?

12:46.099 --> 12:48.101
- WE'RE ALL DYING, DOC.

12:48.101 --> 12:51.646
- SOON?

12:51.646 --> 12:53.231
- NOPE.

12:53.231 --> 12:55.692
NOT READY
TO PUNCH MY TICKET YET.

12:55.692 --> 12:57.235
I GOT A GOOD TEN YEARS LEFT.

12:57.235 --> 12:59.446
JUST GOT TO GIVE
THIS OLD LIVER

12:59.446 --> 13:01.072
A COUPLE OF MONTHS
TO REJUVENATE,

13:01.072 --> 13:02.782
GET ITS MOJO BACK.

13:02.782 --> 13:06.536
- HOW SOON?
- VERY SOON.

13:06.536 --> 13:08.496
"ORDER THE FLOWERS

13:08.496 --> 13:10.498
AND DECIDE BETWEEN AN URN
OR A CASKET" SOON.

13:10.498 --> 13:12.083
- NOT GONNA HAPPEN, DOC.

13:12.083 --> 13:13.960
YOU DON'T KNOW US GALLAGHERS.

13:13.960 --> 13:15.003
WE'RE RESILIENT.

13:15.003 --> 13:17.631
- YOU HAVE CIRRHOSIS--

13:17.631 --> 13:19.967
THE RESULT OF CHRONIC
PROGRESSIVE LIVER DISEASE.

13:19.967 --> 13:21.969
YOU'RE LOSING
EXCRETORY FUNCTION.

13:21.969 --> 13:24.596
YOU'VE DEVELOPED ASCITES,
VARICEAL HEMORRHAGES,

13:24.596 --> 13:27.933
HEPATIC ENCEPHALOPATHY,
AND RENAL IMPAIRMENT.

13:30.018 --> 13:32.145
TIME'S UP, FRANK.

13:32.145 --> 13:34.981
- IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
WE CAN DO?

13:34.981 --> 13:36.733
- MAKE HIM COMFORTABLE.

13:36.733 --> 13:38.360
HOSPICE
IS AN EXCELLENT OPTION.

13:38.360 --> 13:40.237
I ASSUME COST IS AN ISSUE.

13:40.237 --> 13:41.821
THERE ARE
SEVERAL NICE ONES AROUND

13:41.821 --> 13:43.365
THAT ACCEPT THE INDIGENT--

13:43.365 --> 13:45.033
RUN BY RELIGIOUS ORDERS,

13:45.033 --> 13:47.285
BUT WELL WORTH A COUPLE CHORUSES
OF AMAZING GRACE

13:47.285 --> 13:51.289
TO HAVE YOUR LAST DAYS
BE SOMEPLACE NICE.

13:51.289 --> 13:54.167
[chuckles]

13:54.167 --> 13:55.877
PLEASURE KNOWING YOU, FRANK.

13:55.877 --> 13:57.629
GOOD LUCK.

13:57.629 --> 14:00.465
- BACK AT YOU, DOC.

14:02.259 --> 14:06.263
- FIONA GALLAGHER?

14:06.263 --> 14:07.639
- YES?

14:07.639 --> 14:08.932
- ANY MEDICAL ISSUES?

14:08.932 --> 14:10.183
- NO.

14:10.183 --> 14:12.477
- DIABETES? TUBERCULOSIS?
H.I.V.?

14:12.477 --> 14:14.562
FOOD ALLERGIES?

14:14.562 --> 14:15.855
YOU HOOKED ON ANYTHING--

14:15.855 --> 14:19.276
DRUG DEPENDENCIES
WE SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?

14:19.276 --> 14:20.986
WHAT ABOUT MEDICATIONS?

14:20.986 --> 14:22.279
YOU TAKING
ANY PRESCRIPTION MEDS?

14:22.279 --> 14:23.655
- NO.

14:23.655 --> 14:25.657
- PERSONAL ITEMS, PLEASE.
- WHAT?

14:25.657 --> 14:28.451
- WATCH, RINGS,
BRACELETS, EARRINGS,

14:28.451 --> 14:30.120
WALLET, MONEY.

14:30.120 --> 14:32.872
KEYS, ANY OTHER PIERCINGS,
EVERYTHING IN YOUR POCKETS.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.666
- MY BROTHER'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

14:34.666 --> 14:37.502
UH, I NEED TO MAKE A CALL,
FIND OUT HOW HE'S DOING.

14:39.462 --> 14:41.047
- ARM, PLEASE.
- PLEASE, CAN I MAKE A CALL

14:41.047 --> 14:43.049
AND FIND OUT HOW
MY BROTHER'S DOING?

14:43.049 --> 14:44.759
- THAT YOU?

14:44.759 --> 14:46.971
SIGN HERE TO ACKNOWLEDGE
THESE ARE THE POSSESSIONS

14:46.971 --> 14:48.973
YOU GAVE ME.

14:54.311 --> 14:57.982
DOWN THE HALL TO THE RIGHT
AND STRIP.

14:57.982 --> 14:59.774
LET'S GO.

15:07.324 --> 15:09.409
IN THERE.

15:14.957 --> 15:16.959
CLOTHES IN THE BAG.

15:30.722 --> 15:32.724
- [sniffs]

15:45.153 --> 15:47.155
- UNDERWEAR TOO.

15:56.040 --> 15:58.042
ARMS UP.

16:03.129 --> 16:05.090
OPEN YOUR MOUTH.

16:05.090 --> 16:08.343
FLIP UP THE TOP LIP.

16:08.343 --> 16:11.471
FLIP THE BOTTOM.

16:11.471 --> 16:15.225
LIFT UP YOUR TONGUE.

16:15.225 --> 16:17.394
SOLES OF YOUR FEET.

16:17.394 --> 16:21.147
MM-HMM.
THE OTHER ONE.

16:21.147 --> 16:23.149
BEND OVER FOR ME, PLEASE.

16:33.827 --> 16:36.955
COUGH.

16:36.955 --> 16:38.957
- [coughs]

16:41.043 --> 16:44.337
- PUT ON THE UNIFORM.

16:44.337 --> 16:48.967
- [voice breaking]
CAN I GET MY CALL NOW, PLEASE?

16:48.967 --> 16:51.053
- GET IN YOUR UNIFORM.

16:56.058 --> 16:58.060
LET'S GO.

17:11.406 --> 17:13.324
- THEY STILL SLEEPING?

17:13.324 --> 17:15.785
- YEAH.
LIAM?

17:15.785 --> 17:17.787
- SAME.
LIP STAYED.

17:17.787 --> 17:19.789
HE'S GONNA CALL
IF ANYTHING CHANGES.

17:19.789 --> 17:21.791
YOU WANT SOME COFFEE?

17:24.419 --> 17:26.379
SHOULD WE BE GETTING THEM READY
FOR SCHOOL?

17:26.379 --> 17:30.508
- THEY DIDN'T GET TO BED
TILL 2:00.

17:30.508 --> 17:34.137
I DON'T EVEN REMEMBER
SEEING LIAM, DO YOU?

17:34.137 --> 17:37.432
WAS HE DOWN HERE THE WHOLE TIME,
AND I JUST DIDN'T NOTICE HIM?

17:37.432 --> 17:39.058
- I-I DON'T KNOW.

17:39.058 --> 17:41.436
IT WAS
A GALLAGHER POP-UP PARTY.

17:41.436 --> 17:43.438
BOOZE WAS FLOWING.

17:43.438 --> 17:46.274
NOISE WAS NOISY.

17:46.274 --> 17:48.067
THERE WAS A LOT OF SHIT
GOING ON.

17:48.067 --> 17:49.736
- YEAH.
- [sighs]

17:49.736 --> 17:52.113
- I SHOULD'VE NOTICED HIM,
KEPT AN EYE ON HIM.

17:52.113 --> 17:53.948
- [slurps]
IT'S NOT OUR KID.

17:53.948 --> 17:55.492
IT'S NOT OUR JOB TO WATCH HIM.

17:55.492 --> 17:57.076
- IT IS OUR JOB.

17:57.076 --> 17:59.704
WITH LIP OFF AT COLLEGE
AND IAN RUNNING AWAY,

17:59.704 --> 18:02.249
FIONA CAN'T KEEP TRACK
OF THESE KIDS ALL BY HERSELF.

18:02.249 --> 18:04.542
- LOOK, I'M NOT SAYING
IT'S HER FAULT.

18:04.542 --> 18:07.462
I'M JUST SAYING
THAT IT'S NOT OURS EITHER.

18:07.462 --> 18:09.756
IT'S NOBODY'S.
SHIT HAPPENS.

18:09.756 --> 18:11.591
- WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
WITH OUR BABIES?

18:11.591 --> 18:14.469
- THEY'RE GONNA BE FINE.
WE'RE GONNA KEEP 'EM SAFE.

18:14.469 --> 18:17.805
THEY'RE GONNA GROW UP HAPPY
AND SMART

18:17.805 --> 18:20.808
AND PLAY FOR THE BULLS.

18:20.808 --> 18:24.229
ONE OF 'EM'S
GONNA BE ELECTED PRESIDENT.

18:24.229 --> 18:26.231
- OF THE UNITED STATES?
- HELL, YEAH. WHY NOT?

18:26.231 --> 18:28.900
WE ALREADY ELECTED A SKINNY
HALF-BLACK MUSLIM DUDE

18:28.900 --> 18:30.860
NAMED AFTER
A TOWEL-HEAD DICTATOR.

18:30.860 --> 18:35.157
- [laughs]

18:35.157 --> 18:38.160
[El train passing]

18:59.389 --> 19:02.308
[upbeat indie pop]

19:02.308 --> 19:10.316
♪ ♪

19:24.414 --> 19:27.667
[music stops]

19:27.667 --> 19:32.255
- GOOD MORNING, MR. SHALIBAN.

19:32.255 --> 19:34.716
IT'S A SWEAT LODGE.

19:34.716 --> 19:37.010
IT'S GREAT
FOR GETTING RID OF TOXINS.

19:37.010 --> 19:39.929
YEAH, BRING YOUR MOM BY LATER.
WE'LL HEAT IT UP.

19:39.929 --> 19:44.350
I'M SURE IT'LL HELP
HER EMPHYSEMA.

19:44.350 --> 19:48.313
OKAY, HAVE A GOOD DAY,
MR. SHALIBAN.

19:51.608 --> 19:53.693
STINKING WIND!

19:53.693 --> 19:56.405
ONE-EYED SNAKE!
RUNS WITH POO!

19:56.405 --> 19:57.947
BREAKFAST!

19:57.947 --> 20:00.242
- YOU KNOW THAT'S NOT
THEIR REAL NAMES, RIGHT?

20:00.242 --> 20:03.328
- IT'S THE NAMES THEY GAVE ME.

20:03.328 --> 20:06.080
HOW ARE YOU FEELING
THIS MORNING?

20:06.080 --> 20:07.457
- A LITTLE SORE.

20:07.457 --> 20:10.793
VIOLATED, BUT IN A GOOD WAY.

20:10.793 --> 20:15.006
NOTHING I HAVEN'T FELT AFTER
SPENDING A DAY ON THE SADDLE.

20:15.006 --> 20:18.217
- OOH, HOW DO YOU SAY,
UM, "HELLO, EVERYONE"

20:18.217 --> 20:19.260
IN MENOMINEE?

20:19.260 --> 20:23.640
- POSOH MAWANEW WEYAK.

20:23.640 --> 20:27.018
- POSOH MAWANEW WEYAK!

20:27.018 --> 20:28.811
I HOPE YOU'RE HUNGRY!

20:28.811 --> 20:32.565
I'VE GOT, UM, NOKAKE PANCAKES
AND MOLASSES SYRUP!

20:34.776 --> 20:37.445
- SO WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO BE
HEADING BACK

20:37.445 --> 20:39.238
TO THE RESERVATION TODAY,
SAD TO SAY.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.240
- WHAT?
ALREADY?

20:41.240 --> 20:43.159
- THEIR EDUCATION BECKONS.

20:43.159 --> 20:45.161
- HOW FAR IS IT?

20:45.161 --> 20:47.747
- MENOMINEE? ABOUT 90 MINUTES,
DEPENDING ON THE TRAFFIC.

20:47.747 --> 20:49.415
- GOT ANY MRS. BUTTERWORTH'S?

20:49.415 --> 20:51.292
- EAT AND SAY THANK YOU.

20:51.292 --> 20:54.337
IT SHOULD ONLY BE A COUPLE WEEKS
WHILE I TRACK DOWN MY SISTER.

20:54.337 --> 20:56.089
- SHE'S PROBABLY OUT
IN RENO AGAIN.

20:56.089 --> 20:57.340
- LOG CABIN MAPLE?
- [bangs table]

20:57.340 --> 21:00.677
EAT IT!

21:00.677 --> 21:03.638
- I HAVE
SOME HOMEMADE HUCKLEBERRY JAM

21:03.638 --> 21:05.848
IF YOU'D PREFER.

21:05.848 --> 21:07.475
- THEY'RE GOOD.
THEY'RE EATING.

21:07.475 --> 21:09.894
- OKAY.

21:09.894 --> 21:12.730
I WAS--I WAS THINKING, WELL...

21:12.730 --> 21:16.025
MAYBE I COULD COME VISIT YOU
ON THE RESERVATION.

21:16.025 --> 21:17.486
I'VE NEVER BEEN.

21:17.486 --> 21:19.363
- SURE. WHY NOT?
YOU CAN STAY WITH US.

21:19.363 --> 21:21.072
WE HAVE PLENTY OF ROOM.

21:21.072 --> 21:24.867
- DO YOU HAVE A LOT OF LAND
FOR FARMING AND AGRICULTURE?

21:24.867 --> 21:28.037
- WE LIVE IN A DOUBLE-WIDE
BEHIND THE CASINO.

21:29.706 --> 21:31.416
- OH, THAT SOUNDS NICE.

21:31.416 --> 21:33.502
- CASINO HAS A POOL
WITH A SLIDE.

21:33.502 --> 21:34.919
- [gasps]
- AND A GO-CART TRACK.

21:34.919 --> 21:38.256
- LESS TALKING,
MORE EATING, PLEASE.

21:40.758 --> 21:42.093
- THERE YOU GO.

21:42.093 --> 21:44.512
WANT SOME HELP WITH THAT?

21:49.142 --> 21:53.354
[cell phone ringing]

21:53.354 --> 21:55.357
[phone beeps]
YEAH.

21:55.357 --> 21:56.816
- YOU HAVE A COLLECT CALL

21:56.816 --> 21:59.402
FROM THE COOK COUNTY JAIL
FROM...

21:59.402 --> 22:00.820
- [shakily]
FIONA GALLAGHER.

22:00.820 --> 22:03.823
- TO ACCEPT THIS CALL,
PRESS POUND.

22:07.326 --> 22:09.538
TO ACCEPT THIS CALL,
PRESS POUND,

22:09.538 --> 22:12.457
OR PRESS ZERO
FOR MORE OPTIONS.

22:18.546 --> 22:20.965
PLEASE BE AWARE THAT ALL CALLS
FROM THIS FACILITY

22:20.965 --> 22:24.510
ARE RECORDED AND MONITORED
BY LAW ENFORCEMENT AUTHORITIES.

22:24.510 --> 22:26.430
[line beeps]

22:26.430 --> 22:28.681
- HELLO?

22:28.681 --> 22:31.768
LIP?

22:31.768 --> 22:32.810
- YEAH.

22:32.810 --> 22:34.896
- HOW IS HE?

22:34.896 --> 22:35.938
- LIAM?

22:35.938 --> 22:39.400
- YES, LIAM.
JESUS!

22:39.400 --> 22:42.820
LIP?

22:42.820 --> 22:45.823
- HE'S ALIVE.

22:45.823 --> 22:49.744
HE'S IN THE PEDIATRIC
INTENSIVE CARE UNIT.

22:49.744 --> 22:51.996
- [sniffles]
BUT HE'S GONNA BE OKAY?

22:55.166 --> 22:57.084
- SURE.

22:57.084 --> 23:01.756
YEAH, HE'S STRAPPED DOWN,
'CAUSE HE WAS HURTING HIMSELF.

23:01.756 --> 23:04.509
HE'S ON A TON OF DRUGS
AND AN I.V.

23:04.509 --> 23:06.219
AND COULD HAVE
PERMANENT BRAIN DAMAGE,

23:06.219 --> 23:08.221
BUT HE'S GONNA LIVE.

23:13.768 --> 23:14.977
ARE YOU STILL THERE?

23:14.977 --> 23:18.022
- [sobbing]
YEAH, I'M HERE.

23:22.026 --> 23:24.237
[sobs]
PLEASE, PLEASE...

23:24.237 --> 23:25.863
- MR. GALLAGHER?
- PLEASE, TELL HIM THAT--

23:25.863 --> 23:27.615
- GOT TO GO.

23:27.615 --> 23:29.576
- PLEASE TELL HIM
THAT I LOVE HIM, OKAY?

23:29.576 --> 23:31.035
AND I'M SO, SO SORRY.
PLEASE?

23:31.035 --> 23:34.539
PLEASE?
LIP?

23:34.539 --> 23:39.461
LIP!
[line blaring]

23:39.461 --> 23:40.837
- SO HIS HEART RATE
AND HIS BLOOD PRESSURE

23:40.837 --> 23:42.380
HAVE RETURNED TO NORMAL,

23:42.380 --> 23:44.508
AND HIS GLUCOSE LEVELS
HAVE STABILIZED.

23:44.508 --> 23:46.092
THAT MEANS
WE'RE GONNA MOVE HIM DOWNSTAIRS

23:46.092 --> 23:47.593
TO A BED
IN THE GENERAL PEDIATRICS WARD

23:47.593 --> 23:49.220
AS SOON
AS ONE BECOMES AVAILABLE.

23:49.220 --> 23:50.555
OKAY?

23:50.555 --> 23:52.056
HE SHOULD BE READY
TO BE DISCHARGED THEN

23:52.056 --> 23:53.766
IN, LIKE, I DON'T KNOW,
A DAY OR TWO.

23:53.766 --> 23:56.310
- GOOD. THAT'S GOOD.
- YEAH.

23:56.310 --> 23:58.522
UH, PHILIP,
THIS IS MS. MATLOCK.

23:58.522 --> 24:01.023
SHE'S FROM SOCIAL SERVICES.

24:01.023 --> 24:02.608
- ANNE. MR. GALLAGHER.
- HI.

24:02.608 --> 24:05.027
- YOUR SISTER IS
YOUR BROTHER'S LEGAL GUARDIAN?

24:05.027 --> 24:06.779
- ALONG WITH MY FATHER, YEAH.

24:06.779 --> 24:08.739
- WAS YOUR FATHER AT HOME WHEN
THE INCIDENT WITH LIAM OCCURRED?

24:08.739 --> 24:10.449
- UH, NO, NO, HE WASN'T THERE.

24:10.449 --> 24:12.159
- DO YOU KNOW
WHERE YOUR FATHER IS?

24:12.159 --> 24:13.369
- NO IDEA.

24:13.369 --> 24:15.037
- HE DOESN'T LIVE IN THE HOME?

24:15.037 --> 24:18.625
- NO, I'VE BEEN AWAY AT COLLEGE,
SO I-I DON'T KNOW.

24:18.625 --> 24:20.376
- DO YOU KNOW
WHERE WE CAN FIND HIM?

24:20.376 --> 24:21.627
- NO.

24:21.627 --> 24:23.672
- AND YOUR SISTER
IS IN POLICE CUSTODY?

24:23.672 --> 24:25.214
- YEAH.

24:25.214 --> 24:26.757
- YOU'RE GONNA NEED TO FIND
YOUR FATHER

24:26.757 --> 24:29.051
BEFORE LIAM IS READY
TO BE RELEASED,

24:29.051 --> 24:32.263
OR WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO PLACE HIM
INTO FOSTER CARE.

24:32.263 --> 24:33.472
- CAN I TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
FOR HIM?

24:33.472 --> 24:35.349
I'M--I'M AN ADULT, 18.

24:35.349 --> 24:39.103
- YOU'RE AWAY
AT COLLEGE, RIGHT?

24:39.103 --> 24:43.065
- UH, YEAH, BUT I'LL--I'LL QUIT.
YOU KNOW, I CAN TAKE HIM.

24:43.065 --> 24:44.483
- [sighs]
YOU CAN PETITION THE COURT,

24:44.483 --> 24:45.860
BUT THAT TAKES TIME.

24:45.860 --> 24:47.696
YOUR FATHER
IS THE QUICKER SOLUTION

24:47.696 --> 24:49.071
IF YOU WANT TO KEEP YOUR BROTHER
OUT OF FOSTER CARE,

24:49.071 --> 24:50.323
EVEN TEMPORARILY.

24:50.323 --> 24:53.367
- OKAY.

24:53.367 --> 24:54.703
- WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE HIM?

24:54.703 --> 24:57.330
- YES.
- OKAY.

24:57.330 --> 24:59.708
HEY, BUDDY.

24:59.708 --> 25:02.877
- HEY, HEY.
- LOOK WHO I BROUGHT.

25:02.877 --> 25:05.087
- HEY, HOW YOU DOING?
HI!

25:05.087 --> 25:07.465
HI, MONKEY MAN!

25:07.465 --> 25:09.884
HI!

25:09.884 --> 25:13.054
[sighs]

25:13.054 --> 25:16.683
YOU'RE OKAY.

25:16.683 --> 25:18.685
YOU'RE OKAY.

25:23.022 --> 25:24.607
- YOU SHOULD AT LEAST TAKE
A LOOK.

25:24.607 --> 25:25.650
- NO, THANK YOU.

25:25.650 --> 25:27.526
- COULD BE NICE.

25:27.526 --> 25:31.155
- A BUNCH OF CANCER PATIENTS
SCREAMING FOR MORPHINE...

25:31.155 --> 25:33.866
AS TUMORS SLOWLY BREAK
THEIR BONES,

25:33.866 --> 25:36.535
SOME NUN SPRINKLING THE POOR
FUCKERS WITH HOLY WATER?

25:36.535 --> 25:38.704
[shudders]
- [grunts]

25:38.704 --> 25:40.915
[straining]
ONE OF THEM WAS THE METHODISTS.

25:40.915 --> 25:44.710
I DON'T THINK THEY HAVE NUNS.
- NOT INTERESTED.

25:44.710 --> 25:49.131
[bus beeping]

25:49.131 --> 25:52.301
- WHY HAVEN'T YOU ASKED ME
ABOUT MY MOM BEFORE?

25:52.301 --> 25:54.387
- WHAT?
- YOU NEVER ASKED ME ABOUT HER.

25:54.387 --> 25:56.180
- THAT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

25:56.180 --> 25:57.682
- YOU WANT TO MEET HER?

25:57.682 --> 26:00.393
- DID YOU TELL HER ABOUT ME?
- NOT YET.

26:00.393 --> 26:01.602
- PROBABLY JUST AS WELL.

26:01.602 --> 26:04.689
WE DIDN'T EXACTLY PART
ON GOOD TERMS.

26:04.689 --> 26:06.941
- HOW COME?

26:06.941 --> 26:10.569
- SHE TOLD ME SHE WAS PREGNANT,
I TOLD HER TO LOSE MY NUMBER.

26:10.569 --> 26:11.780
- WHY?

26:11.780 --> 26:13.782
- WHY WHAT?

26:15.908 --> 26:19.704
- WHY DIDN'T YOU
WANT TO BE MY DAD?

26:19.704 --> 26:21.747
- WE WERE YOUNG.
IT WAS COMPLICATED.

26:21.747 --> 26:23.416
- COMPLICATED HOW?

26:23.416 --> 26:25.794
- SHE WANTED TO KEEP YOU.

26:25.794 --> 26:28.921
- Y-YOU WANTED HER TO GET
AN ABORTION?

26:28.921 --> 26:30.715
- WELL, NOW I'M GLAD
THAT SHE DIDN'T,

26:30.715 --> 26:31.799
BUT AT THE TIME, HELL, YES.

26:31.799 --> 26:33.217
WE BARELY KNEW EACH OTHER.

26:33.217 --> 26:35.804
- SHE TOLD ME
YOU TWO WERE IN LOVE!

26:35.804 --> 26:38.431
- WELL, IT WASN'T
QUITE THAT ROMANTIC.

26:38.431 --> 26:40.642
WE MET AT A PARTY,
DID TOO MUCH PEYOTE,

26:40.642 --> 26:43.645
AND I BENT HER OVER A DRYER
IN JOHNNY WALSH'S BASEMENT.

26:43.645 --> 26:44.854
- A DRYER?

26:44.854 --> 26:46.230
- I REMEMBER
THERE WAS A TENNIS SHOE

26:46.230 --> 26:47.940
OR SOMETHING IN THERE--
KEPT THUMPING.

26:47.940 --> 26:50.609
[laughing] I BANGED YOUR MOM
TO THE RHYTHM OF THE THING.

26:50.609 --> 26:53.779
OKAY, SAMMI, WAIT!
WAI--LOO--OH.

26:53.779 --> 26:58.284
HEY! IT WASN'T CANDLES
AND BARRY WHITE ON THE STEREO.

26:58.284 --> 27:00.077
WHO CARES?

27:00.077 --> 27:03.497
SOMETHING INCREDIBLY BEAUTIFUL
AND SPECIAL CAME OUT OF IT...

27:05.166 --> 27:08.127
YOU.

27:12.799 --> 27:16.135
- WILL YOU
AT LEAST TAKE A LOOK?

27:16.135 --> 27:17.762
- AT WHAT?

27:17.762 --> 27:19.055
- THE HOSPICE PLACES!

27:19.055 --> 27:21.348
- OH, FOR CHRIST'S SAKE, WHY?

27:21.348 --> 27:23.768
- PLEASE.

27:23.768 --> 27:27.063
- NO.

27:27.063 --> 27:29.816
OKAY!

27:29.816 --> 27:31.484
OKAY.

27:31.484 --> 27:32.651
I'LL GO.

27:32.651 --> 27:36.822
[rock music]

27:36.822 --> 27:38.657
- [grunts]

27:38.657 --> 27:39.658
- WAIT.
"SMALL-BREASTED," YOU SAID?

27:39.658 --> 27:41.452
- YEP.

27:41.452 --> 27:42.787
- I COULD HAVE SWORN
THE GIRL I BENT OVER THE DRYER

27:42.787 --> 27:44.246
HAD A NICE SET.

27:44.246 --> 27:46.665
MAYBE YOUR MOM WAS THE CHICK
IN THE PORTA-POTTY

27:46.665 --> 27:48.793
AT THE ROD STEWART CONCERT.

27:48.793 --> 27:52.213
[lock opening]

27:54.883 --> 27:55.883
- GALLAGHER!

27:55.883 --> 28:03.849
♪ ♪

28:04.683 --> 28:07.686
[buzzer sounding]

28:12.024 --> 28:13.734
HERE TO YOUR LEFT.

28:13.734 --> 28:15.736
YEP.

28:19.198 --> 28:20.574
- FIONA GALLAGHER?

28:20.574 --> 28:22.284
- YEAH.
- MARIA VIDAL.

28:22.284 --> 28:25.538
I'LL BE YOUR PUBLIC DEFENDER
FOR TODAY'S ARRAIGNMENT.

28:25.538 --> 28:26.705
PLEASE, WELCOME TO MY OFFICE.

28:26.705 --> 28:28.791
YOU BEEN THROUGH THIS BEFORE?
- NO.

28:28.791 --> 28:31.710
- ALL RIGHT, IT'S GONNA TAKE
ALL OF ABOUT 90 SECONDS.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.420
THE JUDGE IS GONNA READ
THE CHARGES.

28:33.420 --> 28:35.798
HE'S GONNA ASK YOU HOW YOU PLEA.
YOU SAY, "NOT GUILTY."

28:35.798 --> 28:37.633
THEN HE'S GONNA SET
A BAIL AMOUNT.

28:37.633 --> 28:39.761
THEN HE'LL GIVE US
A PRELIMINARY HEARING DATE.

28:39.761 --> 28:41.763
YOU POST THE BOND, AND YOU GET
THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

28:41.763 --> 28:43.347
- IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

28:43.347 --> 28:44.932
I HAD NO IDEA THAT MY BROTHER
WAS STILL DOWNSTAIR--

28:44.932 --> 28:47.268
- FIONA.
FIONA, RIGHT?

28:47.268 --> 28:48.811
THAT'S A CONVERSATION FOR LATER.

28:48.811 --> 28:50.813
RIGHT NOW WE HAVE TO GET YOU
IN FRONT OF THE JUDGE.

28:50.813 --> 28:53.732
ARE YOU READY?

28:53.732 --> 28:55.693
GOOD.

28:59.823 --> 29:02.826
GALLAGHER,
I'LL SEE YOU INSIDE.

29:02.826 --> 29:05.494
HI, PETE.
HOW YOU DOING?

29:05.494 --> 29:07.705
- STRAIGHT AHEAD.

29:07.705 --> 29:15.713
♪ ♪

29:25.347 --> 29:26.807
[gavel bangs]

29:26.807 --> 29:27.892
- FIONA GALLAGHER.

29:27.892 --> 29:31.395
CASE S6-974356.

29:31.395 --> 29:33.355
- IS COUNSEL PRESENT?
- YES, YOUR HONOR.

29:33.355 --> 29:34.773
- READ THE CHARGES.

29:34.773 --> 29:36.734
- POSSESSION
OF A CONTROLLED SUBSTANCE,

29:36.734 --> 29:38.402
A CLASS 4 FELONY

29:38.402 --> 29:41.989
UNDER 720
ILLINOIS CRIMINAL STATUTE 570.1,

29:41.989 --> 29:43.950
AND CHILD ENDANGERMENT,
A VIOLATION

29:43.950 --> 29:48.412
OF THE RECKLESS CONDUCT CODE
720 ILCS 5 SECTION 12C-5,

29:48.412 --> 29:50.915
A CLASS 3 FELONY.

29:50.915 --> 29:53.918
- HOW DOES THE DEFENDANT PLEAD?

29:59.007 --> 30:01.009
MISS GALLAGHER?

30:01.009 --> 30:02.218
- NOT GUILTY, YOUR HONOR.

30:02.218 --> 30:04.428
- DEFENSE REQUESTS
THE ACCUSED BE RELEASED

30:04.428 --> 30:05.763
ON HER OWN RECOGNIZANCE.

30:05.763 --> 30:07.848
- COCAINE OVERDOSE
IN A TODDLER?

30:07.848 --> 30:09.016
THE CHILD IS STILL
IN INTENSIVE CARE.

30:09.016 --> 30:10.977
- BAIL IS SET AT $100,000.

30:10.977 --> 30:12.020
CHECK WITH THE CLERK TO GET
A PRELIMINARY HEARING DATE.

30:12.020 --> 30:13.354
- WHAT?
- NEXT.

30:13.354 --> 30:16.941
- JACKSON, S4-264296.

30:20.778 --> 30:22.780
- ALL RIGHT, STRAIGHT DOWN.

30:26.158 --> 30:28.036
- EXCUSE ME!
- YES!

30:28.036 --> 30:29.578
- WE'RE
FIONA GALLAGHER'S FAMILY.

30:29.578 --> 30:31.288
- OKAY.
- $100,000?

30:31.288 --> 30:32.790
SHE DIDN'T CARVE SOME DUDE UP

30:32.790 --> 30:34.041
AND STUFF HIS PARTS
IN THE FREEZER!

30:34.041 --> 30:35.834
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO PUT UP
$100,000.

30:35.834 --> 30:38.504
COUNTY ONLY REQUIRES 10%
FOR THE BOND.

30:38.504 --> 30:40.005
- 10 GRAND?

30:40.005 --> 30:43.008
- THEY ACCEPT COLLATERAL
OF EQUAL VALUE--A HOUSE, A CAR.

30:43.008 --> 30:44.969
I CAN TRY TO GET IT REDUCED
AT HER PRELIMINARY HEARING.

30:44.969 --> 30:45.886
IF THE VICTIM RECOVERS...

30:45.886 --> 30:48.013
- LIAM.
- LIAM RECOVERS,

30:48.013 --> 30:50.307
THAT COULD INFLUENCE THE JUDGE
TO LOWER HER BAIL.

30:50.307 --> 30:51.935
GOT TO GO.

30:51.935 --> 30:54.645
- $10,000?
- FORGET IT. WE DON'T HAVE IT.

30:54.645 --> 30:56.230
- WE CAN'T JUST LEAVE HER
IN JAIL.

30:56.230 --> 30:57.941
- WE DON'T HAVE THE MONEY, DEBS.
- WE CAN RAISE IT.

30:57.941 --> 30:59.358
WE CAN SELL STUFF--
- NO! CHRIST!

30:59.358 --> 31:02.027
JUST DROP IT!
FUCK, DEBS!

31:04.989 --> 31:07.241
DEBBIE!

31:07.241 --> 31:09.868
- DEBBIE!

31:09.868 --> 31:12.037
- SMOOTH, ASSHOLE.
SMOOTH.

31:12.037 --> 31:13.747
- LOOK, WE GOT TO FIND FRANK,

31:13.747 --> 31:15.332
OR THEY'RE GONNA PUT LIAM
INTO FOSTER CARE.

31:15.332 --> 31:17.084
- SHIT.
- YEAH.

31:17.084 --> 31:18.877
- CARL, I WANT YOU TO GO BACK
TO THE HOSPITAL, ALL RIGHT?

31:18.877 --> 31:20.337
STAY WITH LIAM, KEEP US UPDATED
ON HOW HE'S DOING.

31:20.337 --> 31:22.548
LOOK, I ALREADY TRIED THE HOUSE.
HE WASN'T THERE.

31:22.548 --> 31:24.049
ALL RIGHT, YOU UP
FOR ANOTHER ROUND

31:24.049 --> 31:26.051
OF "WHERE THE FUCK'S FRANK?"
- YEAH, SURE.

31:26.051 --> 31:28.012
- COULD BE
IN SHEILA'S SWEAT LODGE.

31:28.012 --> 31:29.931
- HER WHAT?

31:29.931 --> 31:31.307
- OR OVER AT THAT CHICK'S
TRAILER BY THE SAVE-A-LOT.

31:31.307 --> 31:32.934
- SHE HOPPED A BUS
BEFORE I COULD CATCH HER.

31:32.934 --> 31:34.143
- SHE'S UPSET.
SHE'LL JUST GO HOME.

31:34.143 --> 31:35.352
- WONDER WHY.

31:35.352 --> 31:36.895
- WHAT?
ME YELLING AT HER?

31:36.895 --> 31:38.689
YOU THINK THAT'S
THE MOST TRAUMATIC THING

31:38.689 --> 31:40.774
THAT'S HAPPENED TO HER
IN THE LAST 18 HOURS?

31:40.774 --> 31:42.318
LET'S JUST GO SEE
IF WE CAN FIND

31:42.318 --> 31:44.737
WHATEVER GUTTER OUR
RESPONSIBLE ADULT OF A FATHER

31:44.737 --> 31:48.198
HAS CRAWLED INTO THIS TIME.

31:48.198 --> 31:49.825
- HOSPICE IS
A PHILOSOPHY OF CARE

31:49.825 --> 31:52.411
FOR THOSE FACED
WITH A LIFE-LIMITING ILLNESS.

31:52.411 --> 31:54.413
WE EMPHASIZE QUALITY OF LIFE.

31:54.413 --> 31:56.790
AND WE NEITHER HASTEN
NOR POSTPONE DEATH

31:56.790 --> 31:59.002
WHILE STILL SUPPORTING

31:59.002 --> 32:01.003
THE EMOTIONAL,
PHYSICAL, SPIRITUAL,

32:01.003 --> 32:02.838
AND PRACTICAL NEEDS
OF OUR GUESTS.

32:02.838 --> 32:05.674
- IT IS SO NICE.
ISN'T IT NICE, DAD?

32:05.674 --> 32:07.093
- YEAH.

32:07.093 --> 32:08.970
- FOLLOW ME.

32:08.970 --> 32:11.263
WE HAVE MEDICAL SOCIAL WORKERS.

32:11.263 --> 32:15.059
WE HAVE PHYSICAL THERAPISTS,
MUSIC AND MASSAGE THERAPISTS,

32:15.059 --> 32:16.518
BEREAVEMENT SPECIALISTS,

32:16.518 --> 32:19.105
NURSES, AND, OF COURSE,
THERE'S A PRIEST ON DUTY

32:19.105 --> 32:22.025
AT ALL TIMES
FOR THE FINAL HOURS.

32:22.025 --> 32:23.942
EVERYONE HAS THEIR OWN ROOM.

32:23.942 --> 32:26.111
AND YOU'RE WELCOME TO BRING
PERSONAL ITEMS FROM HOME

32:26.111 --> 32:28.155
TO MAKE YOU FEEL
MORE COMFORTABLE.

32:28.155 --> 32:30.949
WE FEEL THAT TOUCH
IS A VERY IMPORTANT PART

32:30.949 --> 32:33.160
OF OUR END-OF-LIFE THERAPIES.

32:33.160 --> 32:34.495
HI, GERTRUDE,

32:34.495 --> 32:36.789
MR. TASHEGIAN.

32:36.789 --> 32:38.916
END-STAGE PANCREATIC CANCER.

32:38.916 --> 32:40.584
CAME ON FAST.

32:40.584 --> 32:44.005
SIX WEEKS AGO, HE WAS
SWIMMING LAPS AT THE "Y."

32:44.005 --> 32:46.215
OH! SOUNDS LIKE MELANIE'S
WITH MRS. MCCORMICK!

32:46.215 --> 32:49.009
[gentle guitar music plays]

32:49.009 --> 32:52.888
♪ ♪

32:52.888 --> 33:00.938
- ♪ AMAZING GRACE ♪

33:01.897 --> 33:03.148
♪ HOW... ♪

33:03.148 --> 33:05.150
- DOESN'T SHE HAVE
A MARVELOUS VOICE?

33:05.150 --> 33:06.485
- OH, YEAH.

33:06.485 --> 33:08.195
- TRAVELED THE WORLD
SINGING LEAD

33:08.195 --> 33:09.613
FOR "UP WITH PEOPLE."

33:09.613 --> 33:13.575
- WOW.
- BRAIN TUMOR.

33:13.575 --> 33:15.828
MRS. MCCORMICK'S
BEEN COMATOSE FOR WEEKS,

33:15.828 --> 33:18.122
BUT THE MUSIC SEEMS
TO SOOTHE HER.

33:18.122 --> 33:20.791
- HOW CAN YOU TELL?

33:20.791 --> 33:23.919
- SHE DOESN'T MOAN SO MUCH.

33:23.919 --> 33:27.215
OH, FATHER,
THANKS FOR COMING SO QUICKLY.

33:27.215 --> 33:28.632
MR. JOBAR, END OF THE HALL.

33:28.632 --> 33:31.051
PLEASE HURRY.
HE DOESN'T HAVE MUCH TIME.

33:31.051 --> 33:35.013
- THE HOSPITAL SAID YOU TAKE
PEOPLE WITH LIMITED MEANS.

33:35.013 --> 33:36.140
- OH, YES, WE WORK

33:36.140 --> 33:37.683
WITH MEDICARE, MEDICAID,
THE INDIGENT.

33:37.683 --> 33:39.017
- OH, THAT'S GREAT.

33:39.017 --> 33:41.770
ISN'T THAT GREAT, DAD?

33:41.770 --> 33:44.898
DAD?

33:44.898 --> 33:46.650
DAD?
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

33:46.650 --> 33:48.402
- I CAN'T BE
IN THAT HOUSE OF HORRORS!

33:48.402 --> 33:50.571
- OH, DAD, PLEASE!
- MERCHANTS OF DEATH.

33:50.571 --> 33:52.448
SHE MIGHT AS WELL BE WEARING
A BLACK CLOAK

33:52.448 --> 33:53.866
AND CARRYING A SCYTHE.

33:53.866 --> 33:55.201
- THAT'S SILLY!
THEY SEEM NICE.

33:55.201 --> 33:56.368
- THEY MURDER PEOPLE
IN THEIR SLEEP,

33:56.368 --> 33:58.036
CASH THEIR MEDICAID CHECKS
FOR YEARS!

33:58.036 --> 33:59.705
- DAD, COME ON!
YOU'RE BEING RIDICULOUS!

33:59.705 --> 34:02.958
- I CAN'T BE IN THAT PLACE!
I CAN'T--

34:02.958 --> 34:05.669
I CAN'T--I CA--I CAN'T!

34:05.669 --> 34:08.589
OKAY?
- OKAY.

34:08.589 --> 34:09.673
- I CAN'T!

34:09.673 --> 34:11.341
I-I JUST WANT TO GO HOME.

34:11.341 --> 34:14.219
- OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

34:14.219 --> 34:17.139
I'LL TAKE YOU HOME.

34:17.139 --> 34:20.142
[rock music]

34:20.142 --> 34:27.774
♪ ♪

34:39.703 --> 34:41.079
- [sobbing]
LIAM'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

34:41.079 --> 34:43.832
HE ALMOST DIED,
AND FIONA'S IN JAIL.

34:43.832 --> 34:46.960
[sobbing]

34:52.175 --> 34:55.261
- FRANK!
FRANK, YOU IN THERE?

34:55.261 --> 34:57.180
- ARE YOU SURE
WE GOT THE RIGHT ONE?

34:57.180 --> 34:59.431
- YEAH, CARL SAID
SHE WAS IN THIS ONE.

34:59.431 --> 35:01.225
FRANK!

35:05.938 --> 35:08.274
SHIT.

35:08.274 --> 35:09.816
AT THE ALIBI?

35:09.816 --> 35:11.527
- HE HASN'T BEEN AROUND
SINCE HE STOPPED DRINKING.

35:11.527 --> 35:13.904
- OKAY, SO PARKS,
UNDER BRIDGES, ALLEYS,

35:13.904 --> 35:15.906
THE--THE MISSIONS,
THE MORGUE.

35:15.906 --> 35:19.535
- LOOK, LIP,
IT WASN'T FIONA'S FAULT.

35:19.535 --> 35:21.620
WE WERE ALL THERE.

35:21.620 --> 35:24.623
NOBODY SAW LIAM.

35:24.623 --> 35:26.625
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

35:35.842 --> 35:37.719
[engine revs]

35:48.356 --> 35:50.816
- HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

35:50.816 --> 35:53.235
- [sighs]
OKAY.

35:53.235 --> 35:56.613
- YOU DON'T LOOK GOOD.
YOU LOOK STRUNG OUT.

35:56.613 --> 35:58.282
THEY GOT A REHAB PROGRAM
IN HERE--

35:58.282 --> 35:59.533
METHADONE, WHATEVER.

35:59.533 --> 36:01.159
- I'M NOT A DRUG ADDICT.

36:01.159 --> 36:02.370
- NO?

36:02.370 --> 36:03.453
- NO.
- COCAINE?

36:03.453 --> 36:05.163
- THAT--THAT'S NOT
A REGULAR THING.

36:05.163 --> 36:06.456
YESTERDAY WAS MY BIRTHDAY.

36:06.456 --> 36:08.959
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

36:08.959 --> 36:11.254
I GOT A COPY
OF THE POLICE REPORT.

36:11.254 --> 36:12.588
YOU TOLD THE PARAMEDICS
IT WAS YOUR COKE?

36:12.588 --> 36:14.172
- CAN YOU CALL
THE HOSPITAL, PLEASE,

36:14.172 --> 36:15.299
AND FIND OUT
HOW MY BROTHER'S DOING?

36:15.299 --> 36:16.592
LIAM. LIAM GALLAGHER.

36:16.592 --> 36:19.678
- I ALREADY DID
BEFORE COMING OVER HERE.

36:19.678 --> 36:21.680
THEY SAID HE'S DOING BETTER.

36:30.314 --> 36:32.190
- SORRY. SORRY.
- IT'S OKAY.

36:32.190 --> 36:33.609
IT'S OKAY.
- [sniffles]

36:33.609 --> 36:35.611
- YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

36:37.529 --> 36:40.699
YOU PREPARED TO TELL THE COPS
WHO SOLD YOU THE COKE?

36:40.699 --> 36:42.326
- WHAT?

36:42.326 --> 36:43.910
- IF YOU GIVE 'EM A NAME,

36:43.910 --> 36:46.038
SENTENCING CONFERENCE
WILL GO MUCH EASIER.

36:46.038 --> 36:47.873
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

36:47.873 --> 36:49.791
- THE D.A.'S OFFICE IS NOT GONNA
WANT TO BRING THIS TO TRIAL

36:49.791 --> 36:51.335
IF THEY DON'T HAVE TO.

36:51.335 --> 36:54.796
THEY'LL BE MUCH MORE OPEN
TO NEGOTIATING PROBATION

36:54.796 --> 36:56.214
IF YOU COOPERATE.

36:56.214 --> 36:59.092
GIVES US A LITTLE BARGAINING
CHIP TO WORK WITH.

36:59.092 --> 37:00.844
WHERE'D YOU GET
THE COCAINE FROM?

37:00.844 --> 37:02.429
IF YOU BOUGHT IT
ON A STREET CORNER,

37:02.429 --> 37:03.930
DON'T JUST MAKE UP A GUY.

37:03.930 --> 37:05.557
THEY WILL BURN
YOU FOR WASTING THEIR TIME.

37:05.557 --> 37:08.894
- I DIDN'T BUY IT
ON A STREET CORNER.

37:08.894 --> 37:12.689
- OKAY, SO ARE YOU WILLING
TO PROVIDE THEM WITH A NAME?

37:12.689 --> 37:15.275
- I CAN'T DO THAT.

37:15.275 --> 37:17.277
- ARE YOU SURE?

37:21.448 --> 37:23.742
- YES.

37:23.742 --> 37:25.994
- TIME TO HIT
THE CONCRETE TRAIL.

37:25.994 --> 37:27.412
- OH, WAIT! HOLD ON!
I'VE GOT--

37:27.412 --> 37:31.416
I GOT SNACKS FOR THE ROAD
IN CASE YOU GET HUNGRY.

37:31.416 --> 37:33.794
ROGER, THAT'S FOR YOU.

37:33.794 --> 37:36.004
AND, STINKING WIND,
THAT'S FOR YOU.

37:36.004 --> 37:37.673
AND ONE-EYED SNAKE.

37:37.673 --> 37:39.383
DENISE.

37:39.383 --> 37:41.176
AND RUNS WITH POO.

37:41.176 --> 37:42.761
[whispering]
AND, OF COURSE, SARAH.

37:42.761 --> 37:44.429
THAT ONE HAS
SOMETHING SPECIAL IN IT.

37:44.429 --> 37:46.848
- VERY KIND OF YOU.
WHAT DO YOU SAY, KIDS?

37:46.848 --> 37:48.266
all: THANKS.
- THANK YOU.

37:48.266 --> 37:49.976
- DON'T WORRY.

37:49.976 --> 37:51.311
IT'S PEANUT BUTTER
AND BANANA SANDWICHES

37:51.311 --> 37:53.814
AND CHEETOS
AND SOME SNICKERS BARS.

37:53.814 --> 37:55.732
- OKAY, THEN, HERE WE GO.

37:55.732 --> 37:58.068
- OKAY, GOOD-BYE!

37:58.068 --> 37:59.445
GOOD-BYE!

37:59.445 --> 38:00.445
BYE!

38:00.445 --> 38:01.488
GOOD-BYE!

38:01.488 --> 38:03.366
GOOD-BYE!
- BYE.

38:03.366 --> 38:05.325
- HEY, DO YOU KNOW HOW TO DO
AN ESKIMO KISS?

38:05.325 --> 38:06.952
[whispering]
LIKE THIS.

38:06.952 --> 38:10.414
AND DO YOU KNOW HOW TO DO
A BUTTERFLY KISS?

38:10.414 --> 38:12.874
LIKE THAT.

38:12.874 --> 38:15.043
- SEE YOU
IN A COUPLE WEEKS, WILDCAT.

38:15.043 --> 38:18.296
- OH.

38:18.296 --> 38:21.425
[sighs] OKAY, DON'T FORGET
TO BUCKLE YOUR SEAT BELTS!

38:21.425 --> 38:23.301
DON'T TAKE
ANY WOODEN NICKELS!

38:23.301 --> 38:26.347
[upbeat indie pop]

38:26.347 --> 38:33.311
♪ ♪

38:33.311 --> 38:37.065
- HEY, BABY.
- HEY, BABE.

38:37.065 --> 38:38.316
ANY LUCK?
- NO.

38:38.316 --> 38:41.027
FRANK NEVER SHOWED UP HERE?
- NOPE.

38:41.027 --> 38:44.072
WHERE'S LIP?
- HAD ME DROP HIM OFF.

38:44.072 --> 38:45.615
HE'S GONNA MEET US
AT THE HOUSE LATER.

38:45.615 --> 38:47.242
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

38:47.242 --> 38:49.077
- [sighs] I WAS TRYING
TO FIGURE WHERE WE WERE

38:49.077 --> 38:50.787
CASH- AND ASSET-WISE.

38:50.787 --> 38:52.622
I WAS HOPING WE COULD SCRAPE
TOGETHER 10 GRAND

38:52.622 --> 38:55.959
TO GET FIONA OUT.
- AND?

38:55.959 --> 38:57.252
- NOT EVEN CLOSE.

38:57.252 --> 38:58.503
I CALLED RONNIE
OVER AT THE BANK

38:58.503 --> 39:00.088
TO SEE IF WE COULD BORROW
AGAINST THE BAR.

39:00.088 --> 39:01.382
SHE SAID IT'LL TAKE WEEKS.

39:01.382 --> 39:02.549
- MAYBE WE COULD SELL
THE TRUCK.

39:02.549 --> 39:03.884
- YEAH,
I CHECKED THE BLUE BOOK.

39:03.884 --> 39:05.927
IT'S ONLY WORTH 4 GRAND.
- WHAT?

39:05.927 --> 39:07.262
I PAID 15,000.

39:07.262 --> 39:08.722
- YEAH, EIGHT YEARS AGO.

39:08.722 --> 39:10.682
- THEN IT SHOULD BE A CLASSIC.

39:10.682 --> 39:12.726
CHRIST, I AM TIRED
OF BEING POOR.

39:13.727 --> 39:15.604
- [sighs]

39:15.604 --> 39:17.440
- GOD DAMN IT!

39:17.440 --> 39:20.484
[grunts] FUCKING CANDY-ASSED
MOTHERFUCKING PUSSIES!

39:20.484 --> 39:22.068
GET THESE GODDAMN CUFFS OFF!

39:22.068 --> 39:23.529
I'LL KICK YOUR FUCKING ASS!

39:23.529 --> 39:25.113
YOU AND YOUR GODDAMN
FAGGOTY BOYFRIEND!

39:25.113 --> 39:27.533
YOU PECKER-NECK BASTARDS!
YOU ROTTEN MOTHERFUCKERS!

39:27.533 --> 39:29.701
PIG-ASS PIECES OF SHIT!
GOD DAMN YOU!

39:29.701 --> 39:31.411
[shouting indistinctly]

39:31.411 --> 39:33.455
[car door closes]

39:36.291 --> 39:41.296
[police siren chirps, wailing]

39:41.296 --> 39:43.799
- WHAT, DID HE STAB
SOMEBODY AGAIN?

39:43.799 --> 39:46.968
- BROKE PAROLE,
FAILED ANOTHER PISS TEST.

39:46.968 --> 39:49.221
- SHIT, WHY DO THEY EVEN BOTHER
TO LETTING HIM OUT?

39:49.221 --> 39:52.558
HE'S GOT TO BE 50 OR 60 SWINGS
PAST THREE STRIKES, RIGHT?

39:53.558 --> 39:55.560
- IT'S OVERCROWDING, I GUESS.

39:57.896 --> 39:59.898
YOU JUST PASSING BY?

40:03.819 --> 40:06.279
- UH, LIAM'S IN THE HOSPITAL.

40:06.279 --> 40:08.281
UM...

40:08.281 --> 40:12.202
FIONA LEFT HER COKE OUT.

40:12.202 --> 40:13.578
HE ALMOST DIED.

40:13.578 --> 40:15.622
- SHIT.
IS HE OKAY?

40:15.622 --> 40:18.416
- I DON'T KNOW.

40:18.416 --> 40:22.630
THE DOCTORS SAY "MAYBE," SO...

40:22.630 --> 40:24.047
- FIONA MUST BE A WRECK.

40:24.047 --> 40:25.799
- THEY ARRESTED HER--

40:25.799 --> 40:29.845
UM, POSSESSION
AND CHILD ENDANGERMENT.

40:29.845 --> 40:31.597
- FUCK.

40:31.597 --> 40:33.682
- YEAH.

40:35.559 --> 40:39.437
IAN'S BACK.
YOU--YOU KNEW THAT, RIGHT?

40:39.437 --> 40:43.441
THINK YOU COULD FIND HIM
AND TELL HIM WHAT HAPPENED?

40:43.441 --> 40:45.485
- SURE.

40:50.115 --> 40:53.118
- YO, MANDY.

40:53.118 --> 40:55.704
- I GOT TO GO.
- YEAH.

40:55.704 --> 40:59.082
UH, MANDY.

40:59.082 --> 41:01.167
THANK YOU.

41:19.603 --> 41:23.648
[man and woman moaning
on television]

41:28.695 --> 41:31.531
- IS FRANK HERE?

41:31.531 --> 41:33.950
IS YOUR MOM HERE?

41:33.950 --> 41:36.369
IS ANYBODY ELSE?

41:36.369 --> 41:39.331
[moaning continues]

41:50.592 --> 41:52.969
- JUST GOT HIM TO SLEEP.

41:52.969 --> 41:56.640
TOOK FOUR OXYS, TWO VALIUM--
LOTS OF PAIN.

41:56.640 --> 41:59.768
- LIP'S OUT LOOKING FOR YOU.
- SHH. QUIET.

41:59.768 --> 42:01.394
- FOUR OXYS AND TWO "V"s?

42:01.394 --> 42:04.356
BETTER CHECK
IF HE'S STILL BREATHING.

42:12.906 --> 42:14.366
DID THE SWEAT LODGE HELP?

42:14.366 --> 42:15.700
- DEATH TRAP--

42:15.700 --> 42:17.285
ALMOST KILLED HIM.

42:17.285 --> 42:18.662
HE SPENT THE NIGHT IN THE E.R.

42:18.662 --> 42:19.955
SOMEONE HAS TO TEAR
THAT THING DOWN

42:19.955 --> 42:21.289
BEFORE IT CAN TRY
TO CLAIM ANOTHER LIFE.

42:21.289 --> 42:23.124
- DAD ALMOST DIED?

42:23.124 --> 42:24.918
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT CRAZY
INDIAN THOUGHT HE WAS DOING

42:24.918 --> 42:26.754
BUILDING THAT THING,

42:26.754 --> 42:28.755
BUT IT ALMOST TOOK
OUR FATHER FROM US.

42:28.755 --> 42:31.592
[sighs]
I NEED A SHOWER.

42:31.592 --> 42:33.718
BE A DEAR,
SEE IF CHUCKIE'S STILL HUNGRY.

42:33.718 --> 42:36.304
I BOUGHT HIM SOME MCDONALD'S,
BUT IF HE WANTS MORE,

42:36.304 --> 42:38.014
HE CAN EAT MY BIG MAC.

42:38.014 --> 42:40.726
IT'S ON THE KITCHEN COUNTER.

42:44.229 --> 42:46.147
[door closes]
- CARL!

42:48.358 --> 42:50.527
YO, CARL!

42:51.945 --> 42:53.154
SHIT.

42:53.154 --> 42:56.074
[sultry music on television]

42:58.785 --> 43:00.621
- HEY, I THOUGHT YOU WERE
SUPPOSED TO BE AT THE HOSPITAL?

43:00.621 --> 43:01.955
- THE NURSES TOLD ME
TO GO HOME.

43:01.955 --> 43:03.791
FRANK'S UPSTAIRS,
KNOCKED OUT ON OXY.

43:03.791 --> 43:06.167
- WHO'S ON THE SOFA
WATCHING PORN?

43:06.167 --> 43:08.378
- NEPHEW.
- A WHAT?

43:08.378 --> 43:11.131
- NURSES SAID LIAM WAS
"RESTING COMFORTABLY."

43:11.131 --> 43:13.133
- WH--NO, THE--THE NEPHEW.

43:13.133 --> 43:14.802
- OH, FRANK SAYS HE IS,

43:14.802 --> 43:16.511
BUT HE COULD JUST BE LYING
TO GET A LIVER.

43:16.511 --> 43:18.013
WE ALSO GOT
A NEW SISTER UPSTAIRS.

43:18.013 --> 43:20.765
SHE'S IN THE SHOWER.

43:20.765 --> 43:23.727
- JESUS.

43:23.727 --> 43:25.812
HEY, BUDDY, WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL
ME BEFORE YOU LEFT THE HOSPITAL?

43:25.812 --> 43:27.815
- NO PHONE--
FIONA CONFISCATED IT

43:27.815 --> 43:30.651
WHEN I GOT BUSTED FOR STEALING
SLIM JIMS FROM THE KOREANS.

43:30.651 --> 43:33.153
- OKAY.

43:33.153 --> 43:34.279
- YOU GOT THE MONEY?

43:34.279 --> 43:35.488
- FOR WHAT?

43:35.488 --> 43:36.656
- GET FIONA OUT OF JAIL.

43:36.656 --> 43:38.826
- OH, UM...

43:38.826 --> 43:40.035
NO.

43:40.035 --> 43:41.786
- SO WE'RE JUST GONNA
LEAVE HER THERE?

43:41.786 --> 43:44.497
- NO CHOICE.

43:48.293 --> 43:52.756
- WHY IS THE WORLD
SO FUCKED UP?

43:52.756 --> 43:54.215
- I DON'T KNOW.

43:57.093 --> 44:00.221
- EVERYBODY'S FAMILY
THIS FUCKED UP?

44:00.221 --> 44:02.307
- WELL, NOT EVERYBODY'S,

44:02.307 --> 44:05.351
BUT A LOT OF THEM, YEAH.

44:07.020 --> 44:08.772
OF COURSE,
WE'RE THAT EXTRA-SPECIAL

44:08.772 --> 44:11.399
GALLAGHER KIND OF FUCKED UP.

44:13.777 --> 44:16.279
SO, I'M GONNA
GO BACK TO THE HOSPITAL.

44:16.279 --> 44:18.782
UH, SCHOOL, TOMORROW, OKAY?

44:18.782 --> 44:20.492
THAT MEANS DEBBIE TOO.

44:20.492 --> 44:22.243
- SHE'S NOT HERE.

44:22.243 --> 44:25.038
- WAIT. DEBBIE DIDN'T COME HOME?
- NOPE.

44:25.038 --> 44:27.624
- HEY, DON'T LET FRANK
OUT OF YOUR SIGHT, ALL RIGHT?

44:27.624 --> 44:31.086
WE NEED HIM TO GET LIAM
OUT OF THE HOSPITAL.

44:31.086 --> 44:33.296
FUCK, WHY ISN'T SHE PICKING UP?

44:33.296 --> 44:35.883
DAMN IT, WHERE THE HELL IS SHE?

44:35.883 --> 44:39.094
[cell phone ringing, vibrating]

44:49.479 --> 44:52.482
[gentle guitar music]

44:52.482 --> 45:00.490
♪ ♪

45:38.486 --> 45:41.531
[rock music]

45:41.531 --> 45:49.622
♪ ♪

45:55.545 --> 45:57.755
- ♪ YEAH, HEY ♪

45:57.755 --> 46:01.342
♪ ♪

46:02.803 --> 46:06.431
[sirens approaching]

46:08.766 --> 46:12.729
[buzzer sounds]

46:21.863 --> 46:24.866
[gentle guitar music]

46:24.866 --> 46:32.874
♪ ♪

46:43.718 --> 46:45.971
[elevator bell dings]
- HEY.

46:45.971 --> 46:47.973
- HEY, MAN.

46:47.973 --> 46:49.974
OH, THANKS FOR BRINGING
THIS STUFF.

46:49.974 --> 46:52.018
- YEAH, MAN, NO PROBLEM.
HOW'S YOUR BROTHER?

46:52.018 --> 46:53.896
- OH, HE'S BETTER.
YEAH, GOOD.

46:53.896 --> 46:56.397
THEY THINK HE CAN COME HOME
TOMORROW, SO...

46:56.397 --> 46:57.690
- GOOD, MAN.
THAT'S GOOD.

46:57.690 --> 46:58.983
- YEAH.
- I BROUGHT YOU SOME RAMEN TOO.

46:58.983 --> 47:00.986
- OH, GREAT.
- YEAH.

47:00.986 --> 47:03.279
I'M OUT OF CAJUN CHICKEN,
SO I BROUGHT YOU SMOKED HAM.

47:03.279 --> 47:04.697
- OH, THANKS.
REALLY, MAN.

47:04.697 --> 47:06.783
- YEAH.
WELL, I SHOULD GET GOING.

47:06.783 --> 47:08.493
AMANDA'S DOUBLE-PARKED
OUT FRONT,

47:08.493 --> 47:10.745
AND SHE GETS KIND OF POSTAL
IF YOU LEAVE HER ALONE TOO LONG.

47:10.745 --> 47:12.413
- RIGHT, YEAH.

47:12.413 --> 47:15.042
- OH, BUT MOSS HANDED BACK
OUR KANT ESSAYS.

47:15.042 --> 47:16.584
I PICKED YOURS UP FOR YOU
AND STUCK IT IN THERE.

47:16.584 --> 47:18.294
- OH, COOL.
THANK YOU, MAN.

47:18.294 --> 47:19.587
- YEAH.

47:56.040 --> 47:58.042
[buzzer sounds]

48:01.504 --> 48:03.423
[buzzer sounds]

48:15.060 --> 48:19.397
[indistinct chatter]

48:45.340 --> 48:47.092
- GALLAGHER...

48:47.092 --> 48:50.428
YOU MADE BAIL.

48:52.889 --> 48:54.891
[buzzer sounds]

48:58.436 --> 49:00.480
- [sighs]

49:11.240 --> 49:13.242
HI.

49:13.242 --> 49:15.828
- HEY.

49:15.828 --> 49:17.705
- YOU BAILED ME OUT?

49:17.705 --> 49:19.999
- CARL CALLED ME.
- MY BROTHER CARL?

49:19.999 --> 49:23.711
- SAID HE DIDN'T KNOW
ANY OTHER RICH PEOPLE.

49:23.711 --> 49:25.254
- HE PROBABLY DOESN'T.

49:31.094 --> 49:32.220
THANK YOU.

49:37.308 --> 49:40.895
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

49:40.895 --> 49:43.564
- BEEN BETTER.

49:43.564 --> 49:46.151
- YOU'RE GONNA SHOW UP
TO THE TRIAL, THOUGH, RIGHT?

49:46.151 --> 49:47.568
- YES.
- GOOD...

49:47.568 --> 49:49.154
I KIND OF LIKE MY CONDO.

49:49.154 --> 49:50.530
I'M HOPING TO KEEP IT
FOR A WHILE.

49:50.530 --> 49:54.159
- NO WORRIES.

49:54.159 --> 49:55.993
- GET IN.
I'LL GIVE YOU A RIDE HOME.

49:55.993 --> 49:57.745
- AND I'LL PAY YOU BACK WHATEVER
THEY CHARGE YOU FOR THE BOND.

49:57.745 --> 49:59.039
JUST LET ME KNOW HOW MUCH.

49:59.039 --> 50:00.706
- YEAH, JUST MAIL ME
THE CHECK, OKAY?

50:00.706 --> 50:03.043
I DON'T REALLY WANT
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

50:05.002 --> 50:08.798
[door closes,
engine turning over]

51:07.190 --> 51:10.110
[upbeat rock music]

51:10.110 --> 51:18.160
♪ ♪

52:07.458 --> 52:10.545
- I'M JUST GONNA KEEP
MY BAG WITH ME.

52:10.545 --> 52:12.339
[sighs]

52:12.339 --> 52:15.508
I'M GOING TO THE MENOMINEE
RESERVATION, PLEASE.

52:17.969 --> 52:21.681
YOU KNOW
THE GOLDEN TOMAHAWK CASINO?

52:23.140 --> 52:26.978
[speaking
Native American language]

52:29.272 --> 52:33.693
[chanting]

52:36.821 --> 52:38.823
- [groans softly]

52:46.206 --> 52:48.332
- HEY.
GOOD MORNING.

52:48.332 --> 52:51.043
- UH, HI.
[chuckles]

52:51.043 --> 52:54.380
- YOUR--YOUR PHONE
HAS BEEN JUST GOING NUTS.

52:54.380 --> 52:58.009
YOU GOT A CALL
FROM SOME LADY NAMED SHEILA.

52:58.009 --> 53:00.219
UH, SHE SOUNDED A BIT LOOPY...

53:00.219 --> 53:02.054
- YEAH.
- BUT SHE WANTS TO PAY YOU

53:02.054 --> 53:03.848
TO WATER HER PLANTS
WHILE SHE'S GONE.

53:03.848 --> 53:05.808
- OKAY, YEAH.
SHE'S VERY NICE.

53:05.808 --> 53:07.685
- UH, AND LIP CALLED SIX TIMES.

53:07.685 --> 53:10.938
I DID--I DIDN'T ANSWER,
BUT HE THEN SENT A TEXT,

53:10.938 --> 53:14.150
SAID, "LIAM'S GETTING OUT
OF THE HOSPITAL. PLEASE COME."

53:17.153 --> 53:19.364
- IS HE GONNA BE OKAY?
[elevator bell dings]

53:19.364 --> 53:21.949
- TOO MANY DOWNERS.
- STILL NO LIAM?

53:21.949 --> 53:23.326
- NOT YET, HONEY.
- WHERE WERE YOU LAST NIGHT?

53:23.326 --> 53:25.202
- MATT'S.
- WHO'S MATT?

53:27.663 --> 53:30.207
- OH, YOU'RE MATT?
"THE" MATT?

53:30.207 --> 53:31.459
HOW FUCKING OLD ARE YOU?

53:31.459 --> 53:33.419
- WHO'S THIS?

53:33.419 --> 53:35.963
- OUR NEW BIG SISTER
AND NEPHEW.

53:35.963 --> 53:38.258
- DEBBIE, HI.

53:38.258 --> 53:40.885
OH.
- MR. GALLAGHER?

53:40.885 --> 53:42.428
- LIAM!

53:42.428 --> 53:44.388
[all greeting happily]

53:44.388 --> 53:46.057
- HEY, HEY, HEY!
- LOOK AT YOU!

53:46.057 --> 53:47.434
- HEY, BUDDY!
- HI, LIAM!

53:47.434 --> 53:49.477
- OH, MY GOSH,
I MISSED YOU SO MUCH!

53:49.477 --> 53:52.397
- OH, MY GOSH.
- HEY!

53:52.397 --> 53:55.399
- LIAM IS BLACK?

53:55.399 --> 53:57.026
- HE'S ALL RIGHT.
- GOOD! [laughs]

53:57.026 --> 53:58.402
- HI, BABY.
- THERE HE GOES.

53:58.402 --> 54:00.237
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- LOOK AT YOU.

54:00.237 --> 54:01.614
YOU'RE SUCH A BIG BOY NOW.
- GOOD BOY.

54:01.614 --> 54:04.825
- THAT'S THE FATHER?
- I'M AFRAID SO.

54:04.825 --> 54:07.995
- THIS FAMILY'S HOME VISIT
NEEDS TO GET SCHEDULED SOON...

54:07.995 --> 54:10.331
VERY SOON.

54:10.331 --> 54:13.334
[gentle guitar music]

54:13.334 --> 54:21.342
♪ ♪

55:10.307 --> 55:11.517
- HELLO?

55:19.526 --> 55:22.319
ANYBODY HOME?

55:22.319 --> 55:28.451
♪ ♪

55:28.451 --> 55:30.161
CARL?

55:33.456 --> 55:34.832
DEBBIE?

55:47.678 --> 55:49.513
ANYBODY?
